          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Radium used in early measurements was not purified",
                "and taken directly as radium chloride. Spectrographic",
                "analysis showed 0.4% of Ba, 0.2% of Ca, 0.04% of Mg,",
                "and 0.02% of Si. The second sample was prepared from",
                "20 mg of radium chloride that has been passed through",
                "10 crystallization cycles. Spectrographic analysis",
                "showed no significant impurities."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Two samples, each weighing 100 microg were evaporated",
                "on platinum plates and tested for fission in the",
                "thermal column of heavy-water pile. One had 43",
                "fission per minute, and another one had 18 fission",
                "per minute over the background of 100 fission per",
                "minute. Comparison with fission standards indicated",
                "cross sections of 2.6x10-4 and 1.1x10-4 b. The lowest",
                "value was taken and assumed that that fission cross",
                "section is no more than 1.1x10-4 b."
              ]
            }
          ],
